                            <comment id="10042" author="dmitriy" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2003 09:14:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should we allow for null model argument in the ModelAndView constructor, i.e. ModelAndView(String, null) ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10044" author="alef.arendsen" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2003 09:22:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, Dmitry, sorry, I haven&apos;t been looking at JIRA lately... I&apos;ll fix this next week in the reference documentation (on which I/we need to spend more time anyway!)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alef&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10048" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2003 20:50:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess it&apos;s better to leave the ModelAndView implementation as it is. ModelAndView has a constructor that just takes a view name: This is the one to be used if there is no model.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10050" author="dmitriy" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2003 22:49:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That what I thought. Anyway, Alef, when you fix the doc., can you please resolve/close this issue. Thanks a lot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10052" author="alef.arendsen" created="Tue, 23 Dec 2003 23:53:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the documentation accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10053" author="dmitriy" created="Fri, 26 Dec 2003 01:40:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
